concentration inequality

Let $$Z_1, Z_2, ..., Z_m$$ be $$m$$ [[i.i.d.]] Bernoulli($$\phi$$) random variables ($$P(Z_i = 1) = \phi)$$.

Let $$\hat{\phi} = \frac{1}{m} \sum_{i=1}^m Z_i$$, and let $$\gamma >0$$ be fixed. Then

$$P(|\phi - \hat{\phi} |> \gamma) \leq 2 \exp{(-2\gamma^2 m)}$$

